news.title: Allahabad HC issues notice to Greater Noida authority's CEO over pending land allotments
news.para: "The CEO, Greater Noida, to show cause as to why the undertaking given by him and as recorded in the order dated Feb 19, 2024, in a previous case has not been followed resulting in individuals approaching this court by separate petitions for the same relief," the bench of Justices Manoj Kumar Gupta and Anish Kumar Gupta said on Nov 28.

news.title: Patna authorities check 167 vehicles to curb illegal sand mining
news.para: The SP said three tractors loaded with sand were seized under the Bihta police station area late on Saturday night.

news.title: Kalyan-Dombivli civic body to demolish 47 illegal buildings
news.para: The action will affect around 6,500 people. According to KDMC officials, since people live in these buildings, they will first disconnect electricity and water connections before demolishing the structures.

news.title: Karnataka government explore options to reduce burden of 'unsold' affordable homes
news.para: Data shows the govt is in the process of building 45,000 houses at an outlay of Rs 11.2 lakh per house.

news.title: Bengaluru's housing market faces rising construction costs and high interest rates
news.para: Office-bearers of the Confederation of Real Estate Developers Associations of India (Credai) put the rise in construction costs at 11% this year alone. The reason: A steep hike in labour wages and transportation fees.

news.title: GCZMA imposes Rs 39 crore penalty for environmental damage in Siolim
news.para: Despite a challenge by the violator to the cost calculated, the GCZMA upheld its calculation of environmental costs noting that four different ecosystems have been damaged in the property—mangroves, sand dunes, mud flats and salt marshes.

news.title: New insolvency framework to be creditor-led: IBBI chairman
news.para: "We would be happy if less work goes before the NCLT (National Company Law Tribunal)," Mital said, conceding that the adjudicating authority is now over-burdened. He also rooted for a formal group insolvency framework.

news.title: Ranchi: 1,200 property owners served notice for pending holding tax
news.para: This move aims to achieve the corporation's holding tax collection target of Rs 83.27 crore in 2024-25 financial year, with Rs 56 crore already collected through November.

news.title: Aadhar Housing Finance aims AUM of over Rs 25,000 crore by March 25
news.para: "We closed the first half with the AUM of Rs 22,817 crore (from Rs 18,885 crore as of September 30, 2023). Going by the growth rate of 23-24 per cent, AUM should increase to Rs 25,000-26,000 crore by the end of March 2025," said Aadhar Housing Finance, MD and CEO Rishi Anand.

news.title: Surat Credai raises objections to new jantri rates
news.para: Developers agreed to submit objections and suggestions for revisions to the govt. Preparations are underway to present these objections to the collector. If an appropriate response is not received, Credai members said they plan to take legal action to stop the implementation of these rates.

news.title: Haryana's Kundli to be sixth NCR city for Delhi metro to enter
news.para: The Union cabinet approved this metro corridor on Friday, which is set to become the first-ever corridor to connect Haryana and Uttar Pradesh via Delhi.

news.title: Gurugram: Rs 37 lakh collected in GRAP fines so far this season
news.para: Over half of the fines (56%) were issued to construction sites smaller than 500 sq metres for failing to implement dust control measures. Penalties worth Rs 6 lakh were also levied for the illegal dumping of construction waste, officials said.

news.title: Gujarat: Deadline to submit objections to jantri rates extended till Jan 20
news.para: The state govt announced draft proposed jantri rates and invited online objections for a month until Dec 20. However, the demand for an increased time limit and offline submission was raised by developers and farmers' groups across the state.

news.title: Panaji smart city to get Rs 5 crore grant from central government
news.para: The IPSCDL stated that this grant would be utilised for various initiatives under CITIIS 2.0 to address climate action through a structured, multi-component plan.

news.title: Lucknow development body's societies to get rooftop solar plants
news.para: The estimated cost for these solar power plants is around Rs 4.5 crore. However, the long-term benefits are substantial, with potential savings of 70-80% on electricity bills.

news.title: Gurugram development body starts survey to identify squatters
news.para: During the inspection of Nathupur Road, U and S Blocks of DLF Phase 3, officials found widespread encroachments—portions of the road, as wide as 10 feet and illegal extensions of buildings were also found.

news.title: Odisha initiates application process for PMAY-Urban 2.0
news.para: In a letter to the municipal commissioners and executive officers of the ULBs, Odisha Housing Urban Mission Director, Gangadhar Nayak, asked them to create clear and adequate awareness among the applicants and facilitate them to ensure maximum coverage under the scheme.

news.title: MREAT modifies MahaRERA order on interest to home buyer
news.para: The MREAT said that the reason assigned by the Authority is contrary to the provisions of Section 18 of RERA Act 2016 and it defeats the very object of RERA Act 2016.
